  pages     = {271--280},
  abstract  = {Recent advances in intergroup contact theory and research are reviewed. A meta-analysis
with 515 studies and more than 250,000 subjects demonstrates that intergroup contact typically
reduces prejudice (mean r =−.21). Allport’s original conditions for optimal contact –
equal status, common goals, no intergroup competition, and authority sanction – facilitate
the effect but are not necessary conditions. 

