expectancies about others' ethics positively predicted the degree to which negotiators were dishonest, above and
beyond their own stated ethical views, and that it did so across both distributive and integrative negotiations.
Study 3 provided evidence of a causal relationship between expectancies of others' ethical views and dishonest
behavior by manipulating expectancies. Study 4 provided additional evidence of this causal relationship in a
